channel.title: T2 Error cannot find a fix what so ever any ideas?
channel.description:
I'm using this client: http://www.rune-server.org/runescape-development/rs2-client/downloads/474034-updated-317-client-loading-474-data.html
and this source: http://www.rune-server.org/runescape-development/rs2-server/downloads/398807-pi-reloaded-v2-netty-pc-clan-chat-stablest-pi-can-hold-2000-players.html
Everytime I try to log in I get this in the cmd:
[CODE]Map Amount: 1226 MapID:254 Error: T2 - 65,81,73 - 42,3222,3219 - 0,9,-29,-127,55,-36,39,-102,0,0,48,-98,-121,-32,1,-62,124,-110,0,5,9,-10,-121,0,31,-1,-16,32,-128,0,32,-128,0,32,-128,0,32,-128,0,32,-128,0, Floor Map Loaded: 254 Object Map Loaded: 255 Floor Map Loaded: 256 Object Map Loaded: 257 Floor Map Loaded: 258 Object Map Loaded: 259 Floor Map Loaded: 380 Object Map Loaded: 381 Floor Map Loaded: 382 Object Map Loaded: 383 Floor Map Loaded: 384 Object Map Loaded: 385 Floor Map Loaded: 72 Object Map Loaded: 73 Floor Map Loaded: 74 Object Map Loaded: 75 Floor Map Loaded: 76 Object Map Loaded: 77[/CODE]
I have done research I used google a lot haha. Everyone says change the npc bits to 14 and delete the sendcrashframe. I did all this but still the same thing it logs me in then logs back out. Has anyone found a fix for this or know of a fix?

item.dc:creator: @sk8rdude461 sk8rdude461
item.description:
@sk8rdude461 wrote:

hadlich4:

Why does everyone hate on deathlypvpz so much? Like whats so bad about how they coded it?

Literally everything…

The conventions are terrible, reading the code is a pain because of it.
The code added isn’t OOP, and can be rewrote to be like 150% more efficient.
How the content is added is just wrong.
And not to mention having 15 different revisions in the same server can look nasty when you just mash it all together like hack3r/Trisidia did…
